Key Match Events: Trae Young hit a buzzer-beating 49-foot 3-pointer from just behind the halfcourt line to give the Hawks a 124-121 victory over the Utah Jazz.
Trae Young had 24 points and 20 assists while committing only two turnovers.
Collin Sexton of the Utah Jazz hit a tying 3-pointer with four seconds left.
Walker Kessler of the Utah Jazz made back-to-back dunks to take a 114-113 lead.
Post-Match Reflections: Trae Young expressed confidence in his ability to score with time left on the clock.
Hawks coach Quin Snyder praised Young's efficiency and decision-making in the game.
